  "texts": [
    "The Hamiltonian term proportional to J then takes the form:ĤJ = J 2 √ L k,q S z f,q ĉ † k,↑ ĉk+q,↑ -ĉ † k,↓ ĉk+q,↓ + Ŝ+ f,q c † k,↓ ĉk+q,↑ + Ŝ- f,q ĉ † k,↑ ĉk+q,↓,(8)where the matrix element between the quasi-momentum components of the localized spins and of the conduction electron becomes evident and is equal to J/[2 √ L].",
    "B. ObservablesWe study the following operators.",
    "First, we define the spin polarization of the itinerant electron asS z c (t) = Ŝz c (t) = 1 2 L i=1 ⟨Ψ(t)| (n i,↑ -ni,↓) |Ψ(t)⟩.",
    "(9)In our case, the initial value is always S z c (0) = 1/2.",
    "The second key quantity is the quasi-momentum distribution function of the itinerant electron with spin orientation σ, whose expectation value is given by:n k,σ (t) = ⟨Ψ(t)| ĉ † k,σ ĉk,σ |Ψ(t)⟩."
